				<main><article class="main-content"><h1 class="">News &amp; Events at San Carlos</h1>
        <p class="">Students and staff at San Carlos Unified School District are always up to something new, and we love to showcase their achievements and share news about our schools. Check back here often for all the latest news and information.</p>
        
            <div class="pom-container">
<div class="newsItem">
<a name="March312020SchoolClosureUpdate"></a>
	<div class="newstitle">March 31, 2020 - School Closure Update</div>
	<div class="newsbody">
<p class="">March 31, 2020 </p>
<p class="">Dear San Carlos USD Students, Parents, Grandparents, Families, Staff, &amp; Community:</p>
<p class="">On Monday, March 30, 2020, Governor Ducey and Superintendent Hoffman made the announcement of their decision for all Arizona public schools, including our San Carlos Unified School District, to remain closed for the remainder of the school year.</p>
<p class="">Although this is devastating news because we know school is where our students learn best, we also understand the importance of keeping everyone safe. We certainly want our students, staff, and our families to stay healthy, and so we support the decision announced by the State of Arizona.</p>
<p class="">Please take a moment to read our <a href="https://tb2cdn.schoolwebmasters.com/accnt_321058/site_321059/Documents/March-31-2020-Letter-to-the-Community.pdf" title="" alt="" target="_blank">March 31 Community Letter</a> in its entirety.</p>
</div>
</div>
<div class="newsItem">
<a name="recentscusdannouncements"></a>
	<div class="newstitle">Recent SCUSD Announcements</div>
	<div class="newsbody"><div class="">
<p class="">We invite you to take a moment to view a few of our recent SCUSD announcements.</p>
<div class="pom-container"><p class=""><strong>Internet Service</strong></p></div>
<div class="pom-container">
<div class="pom-container"><ul><li class="">The San Carlos Unified School District, along with the San Carlos Apache College and San Carlos Tribal Education Department, are collaboratively working with the San Carlos Apache Telecommunications, Inc. to determine all students living on the San Carlos Apache reservation in need of internet service. Please read our <a href="https://tb2cdn.schoolwebmasters.com/accnt_321058/site_321059/Documents/Public-Announcement-Internet-Services.pdf" title="" alt="" target="_blank">internet service public announcement</a> for more information.</li></ul></div>
<p class=""><strong>School Closure</strong></p>
<div class="pom-container">
<ul class=""><li class="">Effective March 19, SCUSD will close through April 10. For more information, please read our <a href="https://tb2cdn.schoolwebmasters.com/accnt_321058/site_321059/Documents/School-Closure-Announcement.pdf" title="" alt="" target="_blank">school closure public announcement</a>.</li></ul>
<div class="pom-container">
<p class=""><strong class="">Websites for SCUSD Students</strong></p>
<div class="pom-container"><ul class=""><li class="">Please take a moment to review <a href="https://tb2cdn.schoolwebmasters.com/accnt_321058/site_321059/Documents/Websites-for-SCUSD-Students.pdf" title="" alt="" target="_blank">free websites for SCUSD students</a>. We will begin posting curriculum on Monday, March 18.</li></ul></div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div></div>
</div>
<div class="newsItem">
<a name="extenuatingcircumstancewaiver"></a>
	<div class="newstitle">Extenuating Circumstance Waiver</div>
	<div class="newsbody"><div class=""><p class="">SCUSD and the SCHS teachers and staff are doing their very best to provide access to educational opportunities for students. It is the expectation of SCHS that all students and families do their best to access this opportunity and submit assignments for the 4th quarter of the 2019–2020 school year. Students who cannot submit assignments in Schoology for the 4th quarter due to extenuating circumstances will need to submit a waiver stating the reason for non-submittal. Friday, May 15 is the due date. Please read our <a href="https://tb2cdn.schoolwebmasters.com/accnt_321058/site_321059/Documents/Waiver-Form.pdf" title="" alt="" target="_blank">waiver form</a> for more information. </p></div></div>
</div>
<div class="newsItem">
<a name="seniorgraduationinformation"></a>
	<div class="newstitle">Senior Graduation Information</div>
	<div class="newsbody"><div class=""><p class="">We are all devastated about the loss of our seniors’ last quarter of high school and missing out on all of the activities that includes. SCHS and SC Alternative High School will do our best to make graduation as special as can be given the circumstances. Please take a moment to read our <a href="https://tb2cdn.schoolwebmasters.com/accnt_321058/site_321059/Documents/Senior-Graduation-Information-Letter.pdf" title="" alt="" target="_blank">senior graduation information letter</a> for more details.</p></div></div>
</div>
<div class="newsItem">
<a name="schoolclosureguidance"></a>
	<div class="newstitle">School Closure Guidance</div>
	<div class="newsbody"><div class=""><p class="">We are devastated that we had to cut the school year short while SCHS and SC Alternative school was having one of the best school years on record. As you know, SCHS was rated a “C” school by the Arizona State Board of Education, and we were on track to raise that label even higher. However, more important than a school label is the fact that we are missing being together as a school community every day. We are missing seeing our students succeed in the classroom and on the field and smiling during all of their fun and meaningful activities. We hope that when we start the new school year this fall, there will be a greater appreciation for every day that we get to be on campus. Please take a moment to read our <a href="https://tb2cdn.schoolwebmasters.com/accnt_321058/site_321059/Documents/School-Closure-Guidance.pdf" title="" alt="" target="_blank">school closure guidance letter</a> for more information.</p></div></div>
</div>
<div class="newsItem">
<a name="stopthespreadofgerms"></a>
	<div class="newstitle">Stop the Spread of Germs</div>
	<div class="newsbody"><div class="">
<p class="">We encourage everyone to be smart and stay healthy by stopping the spread of germs. Please see the flyer below for more information.</p>
<ul class=""><li class=""><a href="https://tb2cdn.schoolwebmasters.com/accnt_321058/site_321059/Documents/Stop-the-Spread-Flyer.pdf" title="" alt="" target="_blank">Stop the Spread Flyer</a></li></ul>
<p></p>
</div></div>
</div>
